<subSubSection id="59F4654C560E694DC8DC0421815DFBF4" pageId="1" pageNumber="61" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="115136C7560E694DC8DC04218606FC48" blockId="1.[151,1436,793,1144]" pageId="1" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis id="239AEAD5560E694DC8DC04218253FCDB" bold="true" box="[199,324,829,855]" pageId="1" pageNumber="61">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="D6EE4D44560E694DC9DD042281DDFCD4" authority="Moore, 1888" authorityName="Moore" authorityYear="1888" box="[454,714,830,856]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Teliphasa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="239AEAD5560E694DC9DD04228125FCD4" box="[454,562,830,856]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="61">Teliphasa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="757F4B36560E694DCA22042281DDFCD4" author="Moore, F." box="[569,714,830,856]" pageId="1" pageNumber="61" pagination="199 - 299" refId="ref5324" refString="Moore, F. (1888) Descriptions of Indian Lepidoptera Heterocera from the collection of the late Mr. W. S. Atkinson. In: Hewitson, W. C. &amp; Moore, F., Descriptions of new Indian lepidopterous Insects from the collection of the late Mr. W. S. Atkinson 3. Asiatic Society of Bengal Calcutta and Taylor &amp; Francis, London, pp. 199 - 299, pls. 6 - 8." type="book chapter" year="1888">Moore, 1888</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is diagnosed on the basis of broad forewing, conspicuous discal and discocellular dark spots, a narrow antemedial line, and a relatively broad postmedial line that is curved outwardly at middle. In males, antenna thicker with a row of short cilia along anterior margin (
<bibRefCitation id="757F4B36560E694DCC96049A8621FC2D" author="Liu, L. &amp; Wang, Y. &amp; Li, H." box="[1165,1334,902,929]" pageId="1" pageNumber="61" pagination="119 - 137" refId="ref5167" refString="Liu, L., Wang, Y. &amp; Li, H. (2016) Taxonomic review of the genus Teliphasa Moore, 1888 from China, with descriptions of four new species (Lepidoptera, Pyralidae, Epipaschiinae). ZooKeys, 554, 119 - 137. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 554.6177" type="journal article" year="2016">
Liu 
<emphasis id="239AEAD5560E694DCCA7049B87FBFC2C" box="[1212,1260,902,928]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="61">et al</emphasis>
. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
). In male genitalia, the valva is broad fan-shaped and almost circular; gnathos in form of long, paired processes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="115136C7560E694DC8DC04D2815DFBF4" blockId="1.[151,1436,793,1144]" pageId="1" pageNumber="61">
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="D6EE4D44560E694DC95F04D282A7FC64" authorityName="Moore" authorityYear="1888" box="[324,432,974,1000]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Teliphasa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="239AEAD5560E694DC95F04D282A7FC64" box="[324,432,974,1000]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="61">Teliphasa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
superficially resembles 
<taxonomicName id="D6EE4D44560E694DCADE04D28718FC64" authority="Meyrick, 1889" authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1889" box="[709,1039,974,1000]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Termioptycha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="239AEAD5560E694DCADE04D28049FC64" box="[709,862,974,1000]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="61">Termioptycha</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="757F4B36560E694DCB7D04D28718FC64" author="Meyrick, E." box="[870,1039,974,1000]" pageId="1" pageNumber="61" pagination="455 - 522" refId="ref5277" refString="Meyrick, E. (1889) On some Lepidoptera from New Guinea. Transactions of the Entomological Society of London, 1889, 455 - 522. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1889. tb 00932. x" type="journal article" year="1889">Meyrick, 1889</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be easily distinguished by the forewing costa without a stigma in the median area, and the hindwing with a discocellular spot, whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="D6EE4D44560E694DC88C030A8227FBBC" authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1889" box="[151,304,1046,1072]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Termioptycha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="239AEAD5560E694DC88C030A8227FBBC" box="[151,304,1046,1072]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="61">Termioptycha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the forewing costa has a distinct stigma in the median area, and the hindwing lacks the discocellular spot) (
<bibRefCitation id="757F4B36560E694DC8C50326829DFBD9" author="Liu, L. &amp; Wang, Y. &amp; Li, H." box="[222,394,1082,1109]" pageId="1" pageNumber="61" pagination="119 - 137" refId="ref5167" refString="Liu, L., Wang, Y. &amp; Li, H. (2016) Taxonomic review of the genus Teliphasa Moore, 1888 from China, with descriptions of four new species (Lepidoptera, Pyralidae, Epipaschiinae). ZooKeys, 554, 119 - 137. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 554.6177" type="journal article" year="2016">
Liu 
<emphasis id="239AEAD5560E694DC91503278228FBD8" box="[270,319,1082,1108]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="61">et al</emphasis>
. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
). In male genitalia, the conspicuously subrounded valva and the lack of a costal spine clearly separate 
<taxonomicName id="D6EE4D44560E694DC8E103428271FBF4" authorityName="Moore" authorityYear="1888" box="[250,358,1118,1144]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Teliphasa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="239AEAD5560E694DC8E103428271FBF4" box="[250,358,1118,1144]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="61">Teliphasa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="D6EE4D44560E694DC9B103428154FBF4" authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1889" box="[426,579,1118,1144]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Termioptycha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="239AEAD5560E694DC9B103428154FBF4" box="[426,579,1118,1144]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="61">Termioptycha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
